    • Method Detail

      • put

        public void put(K key,
       V value)
        This method inserts a value into the HashList at the specified key. If the specified key is already hashed to an element, then the collision is resolved by chaining.
        Parameters:
        key - the key where the value is to be put
        value - the value that is to be inserted

      • get

        public LinkedList<V> get(K key)
        Returns:
        returns a list of the values at that particular key.

      • keySet

      • containsKey

        public boolean containsKey(K key)
        Returns:
        returns true if the Hashlist contains mappings for specified key.

      • isEmpty

        public boolean isEmpty()
        Returns:
        returns true if the Hashlist is empty - contains no mappings.

      • remove

        public void remove(K key)
        removes the key and all its mappings from the Hashlist.

        If the key does not exist then this method does nothing.

      • size

        public int size()
        Returns:
        returns the number of different keys in this Hashlist

      • clear

        public void clear()
        deletes all the mappings from the Hashlist.
